            <h2>Catalog</h2>
            <p>Configure a category (folder) structure in whatever way works best to describe your business. The catalog can be structured by use cases, functional areas, technical vs user flows, etc.</p>
            <p>All Artifacts and Diagrams will be stored in the Catalog, providing structure and organization to your business knowledge repository.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Artifacts</h2>
            <p>Artifacts represent whatever design documents your organization uses, whether they be use cases, business rule documents, page wireframes, technical documents, user desktop procedures, etc. Upload the source documents into the Artifacts library for easy access for all users.</p>

        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Diagrams</h2>
            <p>Construct flow-chart diagrams to describe whatever your business needs defining. It could be a desktop procedure, a web application page flow, or pseudocode for a program.</p>
            <p>Diagrams can include references to Artifacts uniting all your disparate documentation in a cohesive way.</p>

        </div>
